}} 'Lincoln' () is a cathedral city and county town of Lincolnshire, England.

The non-metropolitan district of Lincoln has a 2011 population of 93,100; [http://www.lincoln.gov.uk/your-council/information-policies-and-
publications/corporate-publications/ Office for National Statistics : Census
2011 : cited in James Wilkinson : City of Lincoln Council Lincoln Drivers Report
Autumn 2012] Retrieved 21 November 2012 the 2001 census gave the entire
urban area of Lincoln (which includes North Hykeham, Waddington and Birchwood) a
population of 104,221. [http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/census/census-2001-key-
statistics/urban-areas-in-england-and-wales/urban-areas-in-england-and-wales-
